Nikole I really adore and admire you and your channel, but please do not advice people to use toothpaste without fluoride in it unless you have evidence that shows that it has the same effect as traditional toothpaste including fluoride.. I'm a dentist student myself, and the chances of getting cavities are proven to be much higher if you use a toothpaste without Flouride in it. The fluoride ions stabilize the ions (like calcium and phosphate) that our teeth are primarily made out of (Hydroxi appatit crystals). The fluoride stabilizes the pH-levels, which is necessary when we eat and drink acidic and food and drinks :) There are still many options for more natural toothpastes, that still has fluoride in it <3

I'm a little concerned about the hype of "clean beauty," and especially preservative-free hygiene items. Preservative-free items are marketed as "safer," "cleaner," "natural" etc, but they actually are the opposite. Preservatives like parabens are used to keep our products safe by preventing the development of harmful bacteria. Think about how much bacteria gets in your toothpaste every time you open it and expose it to air, or place it on your bacteria-filled toothbrush when squeezing on toothpaste. Parabens are proven to be extremely safe for humans â€” there are many doctors and science-based videos proving this on YouTube, and many articles written on this subject as well.
